      "a_bloom_gap_can_starve_a_colony": "A bloom gap can starve a colony. ",
      "bees_need_nectar_from_earliest_spring_": "Bees need nectar from earliest spring through late autumn. Any 2-week dearth — especially during summer nectar gaps or after first frost — forces the colony to dip into honey reserves. Diverse native plantings smooth out the forage curve so bees always have something to eat.",
      "baseline_maine_new_england_usda_zone_5": "Baseline: Maine / New England (USDA Zone 5). Shift ±3 weeks for warmer/colder climates.",
