      "how_real_echolocation_works": "🧠 How Real Echolocation Works: ",
      "bats_emit_ultrasonic_pulses_20_200_khz": "Bats emit ultrasonic pulses (20-200 kHz) from their mouths or noses. These sound waves bounce off objects and return to the bat’s ears. The time delay tells the bat how far away objects are, and the frequency shift (Doppler effect) tells it whether objects are moving toward or away. In this 3D simulation, each sonar pulse you emit travels outward and illuminates cave walls and moths as it passes them — just like a real bat’s sonar cone!",
      "echolocation_visualization": "Echolocation visualization",
      "sonar_vision_simulator_use_arrow_keys_": "Sonar vision simulator. Use arrow keys or WASD to move the bat. Press Space to emit a sonar pulse. Objects illuminate briefly when hit by sound waves.",
      "change_species": "Change Species",
