      "tiger_moth_jamming_your_sonar_these_mo": "🔇 Tiger moth jamming your sonar! These moths produce ultrasonic clicks that interfere with bat echolocation — a real anti-predator defense!",
      "how_sonar_vision_works": "💡 How Sonar Vision Works",
      "what_you_re_seeing": "What you're seeing:",
      "this_simulator_shows_what_a_bat_sees_t": "This simulator shows what a bat \"sees\" through sound. The world is almost completely dark — objects only become visible for a brief moment when hit by a sonar pulse.",
      "brighter_echoes_closer_objects_or_hard": "Brighter echoes = closer objects or harder materials. Faint flickering echoes = soft-bodied insects (moths). The glow fades over 1-2 seconds, simulating how the bat's \"mental image\" decays between pulses.",
      "tips_for_each_scene": "Tips for each scene:",
      "use_rapid_pulses_near_walls_to_build_u": "Use rapid pulses near walls to build up a detailed image. Find the exit (barely visible — it's open air with almost no echo). Watch for hidden passages!",
      "trees_give_strong_woody_echoes_water_p": "Trees give strong woody echoes. Water pools reflect dimly. Moths flit erratically — they're hard to track!",
      "buildings_give_rock_hard_echoes_street": "Buildings give rock-hard echoes. Streetlights create confusing bright spots. Moths cluster around lights.",
      "fruit_glows_faintly_in_night_vision_tr": "Fruit glows faintly in night vision. Trees are large obstacles. Watch for vines!",
      "place_your_own_objects_and_try_to_iden": "Place your own objects and try to identify them by echo alone.",
      "flight_tips": "Flight tips: ",
      "press_w_to_flap_gravity_pulls_you_down": "Press W to flap — gravity pulls you down! Perch on surfaces to rest and recharge energy. Catching prey restores +15 energy.",
      "fun_fact_real_bats_process_all_this_in": "Fun fact: Real bats process all this information in milliseconds using a brain the size of a peanut. They can catch 10-14 insects per minute in total darkness!",
      "species_comparison_insectivore_vs_frug": "🦇 Species Comparison — Insectivore vs Frugivore",
      "species_comparison_table": "Species comparison table",
      "both_strategies_are_real_insectivorous": "Both strategies are real! Insectivorous bats evolved high-powered laryngeal echolocation for active hunting. Most fruit bats rely on vision and smell, but Egyptian fruit bats are the exception — they developed tongue-click echolocation independently.",
      "flight_energy_mechanics": "🎮 Flight & Energy Mechanics",
