      "back_to_stem_lab_menu": "Back to STEM Lab menu",
      "echolocation_lab": "Echolocation Lab",
      "see_the_world_through_sound_bat_sonar_": "See the world through sound — bat sonar vision, sound wave physics, Doppler effect & acoustic ecology",
      "echolocation_lab_sections": "Echolocation Lab sections",
      "sonar_vision_hearing_as_imaging": "Sonar Vision — hearing as imaging",
      "bats_emit_ultrasonic_clicks_20_120_khz": "Bats emit ultrasonic clicks (20–120 kHz, above human hearing) and read echo delay + frequency shift to build a 3D scene at 100+ targets per second. Donald Griffin coined “echolocation” in 1944.",
      "3d_cave_map_by_sound": "3D Cave — map by sound",
      "each_click_bounces_off_cave_walls_diff": "Each click bounces off cave walls; differential delay between ear canals plus interaural intensity differences locate a surface to ~1 cm. The bat’s brain solves this geometry in real time on a peanut-sized chip.",
      "sound_waves_wavelength_meets_target_si": "Sound Waves — wavelength meets target size",
      "c_f_at_60_khz_in_air_5_7_mm_fine_enoug": "λ = c / f. At 60 kHz in air, λ ≈ 5.7 mm — fine enough to resolve a moth’s wing. Lower frequencies travel further but resolve coarser; higher = sharper but absorbed quickly. Trade-off baked in.",
      "doppler_effect_the_moving_prey_signatu": "Doppler Effect — the moving-prey signature",
      "moths_fluttering_toward_the_bat_compre": "Moths fluttering toward the bat compress echo frequency; moving away stretches it. Horseshoe bats compensate by lowering their call to KEEP echoes in their auditory sweet spot — a biological phase-locked loop.",
      "bat_biology_the_auditory_specialist": "Bat Biology — the auditory specialist",
      "larynx_fires_clicks_outer_ear_pinnae_s": "Larynx fires clicks; outer ear pinnae shape reception; massive auditory cortex parses returns. Bats hear over 8 octaves where humans manage ~10. Tongue-clicking humans (Daniel Kish) use the same trick crudely.",
      "acoustic_ecology_a_soundscape_we_can_t": "Acoustic Ecology — a soundscape we can’t hear",
      "tropical_rainforests_are_loud_in_the_u": "Tropical rainforests are loud in the ultrasonic. White-nose syndrome has killed 6+ million North American bats since 2006; insect populations downstream are visibly affected. A frequency band we never knew about.",
      "sweep_discovery_tune_the_chirp": "Sweep Discovery — tune the chirp",
      "adjust_call_frequency_duration_and_ban": "Adjust call frequency, duration, and bandwidth and watch how detection range trades off against resolution. An open exploration — no score, no single right answer.",
      "cf_constant_frequency": "🎵 CF (constant-frequency)",
