      "migratory_birds_face_growing_dangers_u": "Migratory birds face growing dangers. Understanding these threats is the first step toward conservation.",
      "what_you_can_do": "🌱 What You Can Do",
      "lights_out": "Lights Out: ",
      "turn_off_unnecessary_lights_during_spr": "Turn off unnecessary lights during spring and fall migration (March-May, August-November). Even a single dark building can save hundreds of birds per night.",
      "window_decals": "Window Decals: ",
      "apply_bird_safe_decals_to_windows_bird": "Apply bird-safe decals to windows. Birds see reflections of sky and trees in glass, not the glass itself. Decals spaced 2 inches apart break up reflections.",
      "native_plants": "Native Plants: ",
      "plant_native_trees_and_shrubs_that_pro": "Plant native trees and shrubs that produce berries and attract insects — critical fuel for migrating birds. Non-native plants often lack the insects birds need.",
      "keep_cats_inside": "Keep Cats Inside: ",
      "indoor_cats_live_longer_healthier_live": "Indoor cats live longer, healthier lives AND save birds. Win-win.",
      "citizen_science": "Citizen Science: ",
      "use_apps_like_ebird_cornell_lab_to_rep": "Use apps like eBird (Cornell Lab) to report bird sightings. Your data helps scientists track migration timing and population trends.",
      "support_habitat": "Support Habitat: ",
      "advocate_for_wetland_protection_and_re": "Advocate for wetland protection and responsible wind energy siting in your community.",
      "did_you_know": "🤔 Did You Know?",
      "on_peak_migration_nights": "On peak migration nights, ",
      "over_500_million_birds": "over 500 million birds",
      "are_in_the_air_over_north_america_simu": " are in the air over North America simultaneously. Weather radar stations detect massive clouds of migrants taking off at sunset. You can watch migration in real-time at BirdCast (birdcast.info).",
      "most_songbird_migration_happens_at_nig": "Most songbird migration happens at night, when the air is calmer, predators are fewer, and stars are visible for navigation. Birds use the ",
      "setting_sun": "setting sun",
      "to_calibrate_their_star_compass_at_dus": " to calibrate their star compass at dusk.",
      "magnetic_sense": "magnetic sense",
      "of_birds_may_work_through_quantum_mech": " of birds may work through quantum mechanics. Cryptochrome proteins in bird eyes may use quantum entanglement to detect Earth's magnetic field — making bird navigation one of the few biological processes that depends on quantum physics.",
      "some_bird_species_can_detect_the": "Some bird species can detect the ",
      "polarization_pattern": "polarization pattern",
      "of_sunlight_even_through_heavy_cloud_c": " of sunlight even through heavy cloud cover, using special UV-sensitive cone cells in their retinas. This means that even on overcast days, birds can determine the sun's position and maintain their heading.",
      "the_brain_s_memory_center_is_significa": " (the brain's memory center) is significantly larger in migratory bird species than in non-migratory ones. During the migration season, it actually grows in size, adding new neurons through a process called adult neurogenesis. After migration, it shrinks back. This seasonal brain plasticity is a major area of neuroscience research.",
