      "equal_temperament_12_notes_per_octave_": "Equal temperament: 12 notes per octave, ratio 2^(1/12). A4 = 440 Hz; A5 = 880 Hz. Bach’s Well-Tempered Clavier (1722) sold the world on this compromise. Every note you play here lives on that grid.",
      "scales_the_major_minor_modal_grammar": "Scales — the major + minor + modal grammar",
      "major_w_w_h_w_w_w_h_minor_w_h_w_w_h_w_": "Major: W-W-H-W-W-W-H. Minor: W-H-W-W-H-W-W. The 7 modes (Ionian, Dorian, Phrygian, Lydian, Mixolydian, Aeolian, Locrian) come from rotating the major-scale interval pattern.",
      "chords_stacked_thirds_inversions": "Chords — stacked thirds + inversions",
      "triads_root_third_fifth_major_4_3_semi": "Triads: root + third + fifth. Major (4+3 semitones), minor (3+4), diminished (3+3), augmented (4+4). 7th chords add another third. Pop music = ~6 chords on repeat; jazz uses extensions and substitutions.",
      "harmony_pad_voiced_pads_drones": "Harmony Pad — voiced pads + drones",
      "sustained_chord_textures_the_bed_under": "Sustained chord textures — the bed under almost every cinematic score. Try iv-V-i in minor, or i-VI-VII for that Hans Zimmer feel. Drones in fifths underpin Indian classical and bagpipe traditions.",
      "beat_pad_sample_based_drums": "Beat Pad — sample-based drums",
      "most_popular_music_sits_at_4_4_90_130_": "Most popular music sits at 4/4, 90-130 BPM. Hip-hop ~85-95, house 120-130, drum-and-bass ~170 (half-time feel). The kick on 1+3, snare on 2+4 = backbeat — the foundation of rock + pop.",
      "theory_the_math_behind_the_sound": "Theory — the math behind the sound",
      "pythagoras_500_bce_discovered_consonan": "Pythagoras (~500 BCE) discovered consonance from integer frequency ratios: octave 2:1, fifth 3:2, fourth 4:3. Helmholtz extended this in 1862. Sound = compression waves; music = patterns we agree to call beautiful.",
